        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.633/8–1649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jones</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-16">August 16,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received August 16—2:41 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1802. In Mukden telegram 31, August 12 to Embassy, Ward reported that “I am today
                    informing Mayor Mukden first group staff members and dependents originally
                    scheduled leave Mukden en route Tientsin and Peiping July 27 continue in
                    readiness to travel and it is my desire they depart on Wednesday August 17.”</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated Shanghai 1003, OffEmb Canton 763.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jones</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
